#: Game.Levels.PsetFinset
msgid "# Problem Set: Finsets\n"
"\n"
"You've completed three lecture worlds on finsets:\n"
"- **FinsetBasics**: membership, range, insert, singleton, nonempty\n"
"- **FinsetOperations**: union, intersection, sdiff, filter, subset, ext, by_contra\n"
"- **FinsetImage**: image, forward/backward membership, cardinality, injectivity\n"
"\n"
"Now apply these skills to **fresh problems** with sparser hints and\n"
"no new definitions. One new bridge fact βÄî ¬ß0 βÄî\n"
"connects range to cardinality.\n"
"\n"
"**Note on disabled tactics**: ¬ß1 is disabled throughout this\n"
"pset. Because ¬ß2 uses the same ¬ß3 tactic internally,\n"
"it is also unavailable here. You learned ¬ß4 as a targeted\n"
"simplification tool in FinsetOperations βÄî and it IS a good tool.\n"
"But this pset is specifically testing whether you can construct\n"
"¬ß5 chains from individual lemma names. The skill being assessed\n"
"is: given a membership goal, can you identify and apply the correct\n"
"sequence of ¬ß6, ¬ß7, etc.\n"
"without automation choosing the lemmas for you? ¬ß8 will be\n"
"available again in later worlds. Tactics like ¬ß9, ¬ß10,\n"
"and ¬ß11 are also disabled βÄî you're expected to handle negations\n"
"with ¬ß12 and ¬ß13, and arithmetic with ¬ß14."
msgstr ""

