#: Game.Levels.FinsetInduction
msgid "# Finset Induction\n"
"\n"
"You now know how to manipulate sums and products algebraically βÄî\n"
"splitting summands, factoring, swapping order, peeling terms off\n"
"ranges. But all of those tools work by applying *existing* identities.\n"
"\n"
"What if you need to prove a sum or product identity that isn't in\n"
"the library?\n"
"\n"
"**Finset induction** is the answer. Just as you prove statements\n"
"about natural numbers by induction on ¬ß0 (base case ¬ß1, step\n"
"¬ß2), you can prove statements about finsets by induction\n"
"on ¬ß3:\n"
"\n"
"- **Base case**: prove the statement for ¬ß4\n"
"- **Inductive step**: given a finset ¬ß5 and a fresh element\n"
"  ¬ß6, assume the statement holds for ¬ß7 and prove it for\n"
"  ¬ß8\n"
"\n"
"The inductive step always follows the same **collect-and-close**\n"
"pattern:\n"
"1. **Collect** βÄî peel with ¬ß9 (or ¬ß10),\n"
"   substitute the IH, peel cardinalities if needed\n"
"2. **Close** βÄî finish the arithmetic with ¬ß11 or ¬ß12\n"
"\n"
"This world teaches the complete induction workflow for both sums\n"
"and products over arbitrary finsets.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: ¬ß13, ¬ß14 from BigOpIntro,\n"
"¬ß15 from BigOpAlgebra, and ¬ß16 from MeetFin."
msgstr ""

