msgid "# Finset.sum Sits on the Abstraction Ladder\n"
"\n"
"Remember the abstraction ladder from the AbstractionLadder world?\n"
"\n"
"¬ß0\n"
"\n"
"Big operators live at the **Finset** level βÄî the top of the ladder.\n"
"But they are *defined* in terms of the layer below.\n"
"\n"
"Specifically, ¬ß1 is defined as:\n"
"¬ß2\n"
"\n"
"That is:\n"
"1. Take ¬ß3 βÄî the underlying ¬ß4 of the finset\n"
"2. ¬ß5 βÄî map ¬ß6 over it, producing a ¬ß7 of values\n"
