#: Game.Levels.Fintype.L11_BijectiveCounting
msgid "# Counting via Equivalence\n"
"\n"
"If two types ¬ß0 and ¬ß1 are in bijection βÄî meaning there exists an\n"
"¬ß2 (written ¬ß3, typed ¬ß4) βÄî then they must have the\n"
"same number of elements. The theorem ¬ß5 captures this:\n"
"\n"
"¬ß6\n"
"\n"
"Given an equivalence ¬ß7, the proof ¬ß8\n"
"produces the equation ¬ß9.\n"
"\n"
"An ¬ß10 is a bijection with four fields: the forward map (¬ß11),\n"
"the inverse map (¬ß12), and proofs that they compose to the\n"
"identity in both directions (¬ß13, ¬ß14). Think of\n"
"¬ß15 as saying: there's a perfect pairing between the elements\n"
"of ¬ß16 and the elements of ¬ß17.\n"
"\n"
"This is the formal version of **bijective counting**: to count the\n"
"elements of a complicated type, find a bijection to a simpler type\n"
"and count that instead.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Given an equivalence ¬ß18, prove that\n"
"¬ß19 has 6 elements. Use ¬ß20 to transfer the\n"
"cardinality, then ¬ß21 to evaluate."
msgstr ""

