#: Game.Levels.PsetCardinality.L01_ComplementErase
msgid "# Problem Set: Cardinality and Counting\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the cardinality problem set. You'll apply skills from\n"
"Cardinality, the Abstraction Ladder, Fintype, and Counting Types\n"
"to **fresh problems** with sparser hints.\n"
"\n"
"**The collect-and-close strategy**: Most cardinality proofs in this\n"
"problem set follow a common pattern: (1) identify which card lemmas\n"
"are needed, (2) bring each into context with ¬ß0, (3) let ¬ß1\n"
"combine the arithmetic. We call this **collect-and-close** βÄî collect\n"
"the card facts, then close with ¬ß2. You'll use this pattern\n"
"throughout the problem set.\n"
"\n"
"**Your first task**: Given two finsets ¬ß3 and ¬ß4 with known sizes\n"
"and known overlap, and an element ¬ß5 that belongs to ¬ß6,\n"
"compute the cardinality of ¬ß7 with ¬ß8 removed.\n"
"\n"
"Two counting ideas work together here:\n"
"- **Complement counting** tells you ¬ß9 from ¬ß10 and ¬ß11\n"
"- **Erase counting** tells you what removing one element does to the count\n"
"\n"
"Bring both facts into context with ¬ß12, then let ¬ß13 combine\n"
"them with the given sizes."
msgstr ""

