#: Game.Levels.SummationFormulas.L01_ConstantSum
msgid "# Natural Number Induction for Sums\n"
"\n"
"In the FinsetInduction world, you proved sum identities by induction on\n"
"an *arbitrary finset* ¬ß0 using ¬ß1. The base case was\n"
"¬ß2 and the step was ¬ß3.\n"
"\n"
"In this world, you'll prove **classical summation formulas** βÄî identities\n"
"about ¬ß4 βÄî using a different pattern: **natural\n"
"number induction** combined with ¬ß5.\n"
"\n"
"The idea: sums over ¬ß6 are naturally indexed by ¬ß7, so\n"
"you induct on ¬ß8 directly:\n"
"\n"
"- **Base case** (¬ß9): ¬ß10 gives\n"
"  ¬ß11\n"
"\n"
"- **Inductive step** (¬ß12): ¬ß13 gives\n"
"  ¬ß14\n"
"\n"
"  Then substitute the induction hypothesis for the remaining sum,\n"
