#: Game.Levels.FinNavigation
msgid "# Navigating Fin\n"
"\n"
"You've learned to construct and compare elements of ¬ß0. Now\n"
"you'll learn to *navigate* within ¬ß1 βÄî accessing specific\n"
"landmark elements and moving between ¬ß2 and ¬ß3.\n"
"\n"
"Three functions form the navigation toolkit:\n"
"\n"
"**¬ß4** βÄî the maximum element of ¬ß5, with\n"
"value ¬ß6. It's the boundary element, sitting at the top.\n"
"\n"
"**¬ß7** βÄî embeds ¬ß8 into ¬ß9 by keeping\n"
"the same value but relaxing the bound. If ¬ß10 has value\n"
"¬ß11, then ¬ß12 also has value ¬ß13.\n"
"\n"
"**¬ß14** βÄî moves forward: if ¬ß15 has value ¬ß16,\n"
"then ¬ß17 has value ¬ß18.\n"
"\n"
"Both ¬ß19 and ¬ß20 send ¬ß21 βÄî they\n"
"increase the type's size by 1 βÄî but they do different things to\n"
"the value: ¬ß22 preserves it, ¬ß23 increments it.\n"
"\n"
"(This is why ¬ß24 starts at 0: the embedding ¬ß25\n"
"preserves values exactly, and ¬ß26 increments by exactly 1. With\n"
"1-indexing, these clean relationships would need offsets.)\n"
"\n"
"The central insight of this world: ¬ß27 has **two**\n"
"decompositions:\n"
"- Every element is either ¬ß28 or ¬ß29\n"
"  for some ¬ß30 (**castSucc/last**)\n"
"- Every element is either ¬ß31 or ¬ß32\n"
"  for some ¬ß33 (**0/succ**)\n"
"\n"
"These dual decompositions will power the two ways to build\n"
"tuples in the next world.\n"
"\n"
"In this world, you'll learn to:\n"
"- Compute the value of ¬ß34, ¬ß35, and ¬ß36 using their\n"
"  val lemmas\n"
"- Prove that ¬ß37 never reaches ¬ß38 (and ¬ß39 never\n"
"  reaches ¬ß40)\n"
"- Prove that both ¬ß41 and ¬ß42 are injective\n"
"- Prove both the castSucc/last and 0/succ decompositions\n"
"- Prove that ¬ß43 hits every non-last element (surjectivity)\n"
"- Combine all of this in the boss"
msgstr ""

