#: Game.Levels.FinsetBasics
msgid "# Finset Basics: Finite Sets\n"
"\n"
"In Phase 1, you learned about ¬ß0 βÄî a finite *index type* where\n"
"each element is a number with a bound proof. Functions ¬ß1\n"
"gave you *ordered tuples*: data accessed by position.\n"
"\n"
"But not everything in mathematics has a natural ordering. The set of\n"
"prime divisors of 30 is ¬ß2 βÄî there's no reason 2 should\n"
"come 'first'. The elements of a group satisfying some property form a\n"
"*collection defined by membership*, not by position.\n"
"\n"
"This is where ¬ß3 comes in. A ¬ß4 is an **unordered finite\n"
"collection** of elements from ¬ß5, with no duplicates and decidable\n"
"membership. Think of it as a mathematical finite set, formalized.\n"
"\n"
"The key operations:\n"
"- **Literal notation**: ¬ß6 builds a concrete finset\n"
"- **¬ß7**: the empty finset\n"
"- **¬ß8**: add an element (no-op if already present)\n"
"- **¬ß9**: the set ¬ß10\n"
"\n"
"The key proof move: to show ¬ß11, unfold the set structure using\n"
"*membership lemmas* (¬ß12, ¬ß13,\n"
"¬ß14) until the goal reduces to something ¬ß15 or\n"
"¬ß16 can close.\n"
"\n"
"The bridge from Phase 1: ¬ß17 contains exactly the same\n"
"elements as ¬ß18 βÄî the numbers ¬ß19 through ¬ß20. Where ¬ß21\n"
"gave you *indexed access* (¬ß22 for ¬ß23), ¬ß24\n"
"gives you *membership* (¬ß25). Same elements,\n"
"different interface.\n"
"\n"
"In this world you'll learn to prove membership, non-membership,\n"
"and basic structural facts about finsets. The boss at the end\n"
"combines all these moves."
msgstr ""

