"when they're the same number. So why does Lean need a lemma for this?\n"
"\n"
"Because ¬ß6 is a **subtype** βÄî a wrapper around a natural number\n"
"and a proof. An element ¬ß7 is really ¬ß8:\n"
"a number *packaged with* a proof that it's in range. Lean's type\n"
"system distinguishes between the *wrapper* ¬ß9 and the *contained\n"
