#: Game.Levels.Cardinality.L24_Capstone
msgid "# The Capstone Theorem\n"
"\n"
"You've assembled all the pieces. Now for the punchline.\n"
"\n"
"For finite types, **injectivity implies surjectivity**. If\n"
"¬ß0 is injective (different inputs give different\n"
"outputs), then ¬ß1 is also surjective (every output is hit).\n"
"\n"
"Why? The image ¬ß2 satisfies:\n"
"- It has ¬ß3 elements (by ¬ß4, since ¬ß5 is injective)\n"
"- It is a subset of ¬ß6 (by ¬ß7, since everything\n"
"  lives in the universe)\n"
"\n"
"A subset with the same number of elements as the whole must BE the\n"
"whole. This is ¬ß8:\n"
"\n"
"¬ß9\n"
"\n"
"If a subset is at least as large as its superset, they're equal.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that if ¬ß10 is injective, then\n"
"the image of ¬ß11 under ¬ß12 equals ¬ß13 βÄî meaning ¬ß14 hits every\n"
"element."
