#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L08_Extensionality
msgid "The ¬ß0 tactic is the standard way to prove finset equality in Lean.\n"
"The pattern:\n"
"\n"
"1. ¬ß1 βÄî introduces a variable ¬ß2 and converts ¬ß3 to ¬ß4\n"
"2. ¬ß5 βÄî splits the biconditional into two implications\n"
"3. Prove each direction\n"
"\n"
"In this level, the hypotheses ¬ß6 and ¬ß7 handed you the\n"
"implications directly. In the next level, you'll prove an abstract\n"
"set identity where you need to do the element-chasing yourself.\n"
"\n"
"The key insight: *finsets are determined by their elements*. This is\n"
"the **extensionality principle** βÄî two collections are equal when they\n"
"have the same members.\n"
"\n"
"**¬ß8 as a transferable strategy**: This is the third time you've\n"
"used ¬ß9, and each time it does the same thing in a different context:\n"
"- **Fin elements** (MeetFin L15): ¬ß10 reduces ¬ß11 to ¬ß12\n"
"  βÄî two indices are equal when their values are equal\n"
"- **Functions** (FinTuples L12): ¬ß13 reduces ¬ß14 to ¬ß15\n"
"  βÄî two functions are equal when they agree at every input\n"
"- **Finsets** (this level): ¬ß16 reduces ¬ß17 to ¬ß18\n"
"  βÄî two sets are equal when they have the same elements\n"
"\n"
"The unifying principle: **ext reduces equality of structured types to\n"
"equality of components**. Whenever you see ¬ß19 for a structured\n"
"type, try ¬ß20 βÄî it will find the right decomposition automatically.\n"
"\n"
"**Why extensionality?** This is a design choice, not an inevitability.\n"
"A list like ¬ß21 is different from ¬ß22 βÄî lists track\n"
"multiplicity and order. A *multiset* like ¬ß23 differs from\n"
"¬ß24 βÄî multisets track multiplicity but not order. A finset\n"
"like ¬ß25 equals ¬ß26 βÄî finsets track neither multiplicity\n"
"nor order, only *which elements are present*. Extensionality is what\n"
"makes a finset a finset rather than a list or multiset.\n"
"\n"
"**The ext-unfold-logic recipe**: From now on, most set identity proofs\n"
"will follow the same three-phase pattern:\n"
"1. **ext** βÄî ¬ß27 reduces set equality to element-wise logic\n"
"2. **unfold** βÄî ¬ß28, ¬ß29, etc.\n"
"   (or ¬ß30) to convert membership into pure logic\n"
"3. **logic** βÄî ¬ß31, ¬ß32, ¬ß33/¬ß34,\n"
"   ¬ß35/¬ß36 to prove the resulting propositional equivalence\n"
"\n"
"We'll call this the **ext-unfold-logic** recipe. Every set identity in\n"
"the remaining levels follows this recipe. When you see a finset equality\n"
"to prove, think 'ext-unfold-logic' and the three steps will guide you."
msgstr ""

