#: Game.Levels.MeetFin.L17_TwoElements
msgid "You've just performed **exhaustive case analysis** on ¬ß0.\n"
"\n"
"The strategy βÄî which we'll call **Fin case analysis** βÄî is:\n"
"1. **Destructure** the ¬ß1 element (Level 16)\n"
"2. **Case-split** on the natural number (nested ¬ß2 as needed)\n"
"3. **Handle** each case: valid cases with ¬ß3/¬ß4 + ¬ß5,\n"
"   impossible cases with ¬ß6 + ¬ß7\n"
"\n"
"**Why does this work?** Exhaustive case analysis on ¬ß8 terminates\n"
"because ¬ß9 bounds the natural number. Each ¬ß10 step peels\n"
"off one possible value (0, then 1, then 2, ...), and the ¬ß11\n"
"bound ensures that after ¬ß12 valid cases, the remaining case is\n"
"impossible βÄî the value would need to be βâΞ ¬ß13, contradicting ¬ß14.\n"
"This is the **Fin contradiction pattern** from Level 13 applied to the\n"
"impossible branch. This termination is what makes ¬ß15 a *finite*\n"
"type in a proof-relevant sense: you can enumerate all elements and\n"
"handle each one. This idea will be formalized as ¬ß16 in a later\n"
"world.\n"
"\n"
"This strategy works for any ¬ß17 by nesting enough ¬ß18 on the\n"
"natural number. But imagine doing this for ¬ß19: you'd need 100\n"
"branches, 99 of which are contradiction proofs. The ¬ß20 tactic\n"
