"How do you prove ¬ß2 for ¬ß3 elements? In Lean, ¬ß4 is\n"
"defined as ¬ß5 βÄî a function that takes an equality proof\n"
"and derives a contradiction.\n"
"\n"
"The strategy is:\n"
"1. ¬ß6 βÄî assume ¬ß7 (giving ¬ß8)\n"
"2. ¬ß9 βÄî Lean checks if the constructors match; if the underlying\n"
"   values differ, it closes the goal automatically\n"
"\n"
"When ¬ß10 and ¬ß11 as natural numbers, ¬ß12\n"
"performs *injection* βÄî it sees the values inside the constructors don't\n"
"match and derives a contradiction. This is the same idea as ¬ß13\n"
"in reverse: if the values differ, the elements can't be equal.\n"
