#: Game.Levels.PsetFin.L16_SimplePigeonhole
msgid "# The Simplest Pigeonhole\n"
"\n"
"The **pigeonhole principle** says: if you have ¬ß0 pigeons\n"
"and only ¬ß1 pigeonholes, at least two pigeons must share a hole.\n"
"The name comes from the image of pigeons roosting: with more\n"
"birds than holes, some hole gets crowded.\n"
"\n"
"More precisely: any function ¬ß2 with ¬ß3\n"
"fails to be injective βÄî there exist distinct ¬ß4 with\n"
"¬ß5.\n"
"\n"
"Before tackling the full 3-pigeons-2-holes version, let's practice\n"
"the pattern on the simplest case: **2 pigeons, 1 hole**.\n"
"\n"
"Any function ¬ß6 must send two different inputs\n"
"to the same output. Why? Because ¬ß7 has only ONE element\n"
"(the value ¬ß8), so both ¬ß9 and ¬ß10 must equal ¬ß11.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**:\n"
"1. The witnesses are ¬ß12 and ¬ß13 (the two inputs)\n"
"2. They're different (the inequality ¬ß14)\n"
"3. Both map to the unique output\n"
"\n"
"The 'classify + compare' pattern:\n"
"- Every ¬ß15 element is ¬ß16 (classify)\n"
"- So ¬ß17 and ¬ß18 (compare)\n"
"- Therefore ¬ß19 (collision found)"
