#: Game.Levels.MeetFin.L19_ModularArithmetic
msgid "# Enrichment: Fin Has Arithmetic\n"
"\n"
"*This level is an enrichment aside βÄî a mathematical surprise that\n"
"connects ¬ß0 to a different area of mathematics. The main course\n"
"path resumes in the next level.*\n"
"\n"
"You've been treating ¬ß1 as an index set βÄî a collection of\n"
"positions ¬ß2. But ¬ß3 also supports **arithmetic**,\n"
"and it works differently from natural number arithmetic.\n"
"\n"
"What is ¬ß4 in ¬ß5? On natural numbers, it's ¬ß6. But ¬ß7\n"
"only has elements ¬ß8 βÄî there is no ¬ß9. Addition on\n"
"¬ß10 **wraps around**: it takes the result modulo ¬ß11.\n"
"\n"
"So ¬ß12 because ¬ß13.\n"
"This is **modular arithmetic** βÄî the arithmetic of clocks, cyclic\n"
"groups, and the integers mod ¬ß14.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Find two elements ¬ß15 such that\n"
"¬ß16 (their sum wraps around to zero) and their natural\n"
"number values sum to ¬ß17.\n"
"\n"
"(Hint: on a 5-hour clock, which two different hours are diametrically\n"
"opposite βÄî summing to a full rotation?)"
msgstr ""

#. ¬ß0: `Fin 0`
#. ¬ß1: `False`
#. ¬ß2: `False`
#. ¬ß3: `42 = 0`
#. ¬ß4: `i : Fin 0`
#. ¬ß5: `42 = 0`
#. ¬ß6: `i`
#. ¬ß7: `have h := i.isLt`
#. ¬ß8: `omega`
#. ¬ß9: `omega`
#. ¬ß10: `42 = 0`
#: Game.Levels.MeetFin.L14_ExplosionPrinciple
msgid "# The Explosion Principle\n"
"\n"
"In Level 13, you proved that ¬ß0 leads to ¬ß1. But why is\n"
"that useful? Because from ¬ß2, you can prove **anything**.\n"
"\n"
"This is the *explosion principle* (ex falso quodlibet): a false\n"
"hypothesis implies every statement. If your context contains a\n"
"contradiction, every goal is provable.\n"
"\n"
"Here the goal is ¬ß3 βÄî obviously false in normal mathematics.\n"
"But you have ¬ß4, which is a contradiction (no natural\n"
"number is less than 0). From this contradictory hypothesis, even\n"
"¬ß5 follows.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**: Extract the contradiction from ¬ß6 the same way\n"
"you did in Level 13 (¬ß7 then ¬ß8), and ¬ß9\n"
"will close the goal βÄî it sees that the hypotheses are contradictory\n"
"and doesn't even need to engage with ¬ß10."
msgstr ""

