#: Game.Levels.MeetFin.L18_CaseAnalysisPractice
msgid "# Practice: Case Analysis on Fin 3\n"
"\n"
"In Level 17, you exhausted all cases of ¬ß0 (two valid, one\n"
"impossible). Now try ¬ß1 βÄî the same strategy with one more valid\n"
"case.\n"
"\n"
"**Why are some tactics disabled?** You might wonder why tactics like\n"
"¬ß2, ¬ß3, and ¬ß4 are unavailable. These tactics\n"
"can automate case analysis and arithmetic in one step βÄî which is\n"
"exactly why they're disabled here. The manual approach forces you to\n"
"understand *what* the automation does: destructure the ¬ß5 element,\n"
"split on the natural number, handle each valid case, and dismiss\n"
"impossible cases with ¬ß6. Once you understand this structure,\n"
"you'll appreciate the automation when it's unlocked later. The\n"
"automation doesn't replace this understanding βÄî it just lets you\n"
"skip the mechanical parts once you've mastered them.\n"
"\n"
"The pattern is the same:\n"
"1. **Destructure**: ¬ß7\n"
"2. **Case-split on ¬ß8**: ¬ß9\n"
"3. **Nest further** as needed\n"
"4. **Valid cases**: ¬ß10/¬ß11 + ¬ß12\n"
"5. **Impossible cases**: ¬ß13\n"
"\n"
"For ¬ß14, you'll have three valid cases (¬ß15) and one\n"
"impossible case (¬ß16).\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that every element of ¬ß17 is ¬ß18, ¬ß19, or ¬ß20."
msgstr ""

