#: Game.Levels.Cardinality
msgid "# Cardinality: Counting Elements\n"
"\n"
"You've been building finsets, proving membership, computing unions and\n"
"intersections, and mapping functions over them. But you haven't yet\n"
"asked: **how many elements does a finset contain?**\n"
"\n"
"The answer is ¬ß0 βÄî the cardinality function. For any finset\n"
"¬ß1, the expression ¬ß2 returns a natural number: the count of\n"
"elements in ¬ß3.\n"
"\n"
"This world covers the **card_* lemma family** βÄî the toolkit for\n"
"computing and reasoning about cardinalities:\n"
"\n"
"**Building up**:\n"
"- ¬ß4: ¬ß5\n"
"- ¬ß6: ¬ß7\n"
"- ¬ß8: inserting a new element adds 1\n"
"- ¬ß9: ¬ß10\n"
"\n"
"**Taking apart**:\n"
"- ¬ß11: erasing an element subtracts 1\n"
"\n"
"**Connecting**:\n"
"- ¬ß12: positive cardinality βÜî nonempty (both directions)\n"
"- ¬ß13: zero cardinality βÜî empty\n"
"\n"
"**Comparing**:\n"
"- ¬ß14: subsets have smaller (or equal) cardinality\n"
"\n"
"**Combining**:\n"
"- ¬ß15: the inclusion-exclusion formula\n"
"- ¬ß16: simplified form for disjoint sets\n"
"- ¬ß17: complement counting\n"
"- ¬ß18: the multiplication principle\n"
"\n"
"**Deriving**:\n"
"- Why inclusion-exclusion holds βÄî derived from disjoint union and\n"
"  complement counting\n"
"\n"
"**Applying**:\n"
"- The **abstract pigeonhole principle** via cardinality βÄî proving\n"
"  that more inputs than outputs forces a collision, without any\n"
"  case analysis\n"
"- The **capstone theorem**: for finite types, injective iff\n"
"  surjective βÄî the mathematical climax of Phases 1-3\n"
"\n"
"The proof pattern throughout: bring a card lemma into the context\n"
"with ¬ß19, then use ¬ß20 to handle the arithmetic.\n"
"\n"
"You already met ¬ß21 and ¬ß22 in the Image world.\n"
"This world develops the full toolkit."
msgstr ""

