#: Game.Levels.FinTuples.L21_Boss
msgid "Congratulations βÄî you've completed **Fin Tuples**!\n"
"\n"
"Here's your tuple toolkit:\n"
"\n"
"| Tool | What it does | Learned in |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| ¬ß0 | Build tuple with vec notation | Levels 1-2 |\n"
"| ¬ß1 + ¬ß2 | Construct and verify a tuple | Level 3 |\n"
"| ¬ß3 | Prepend element to tuple | Level 4 |\n"
"| ¬ß4 | ¬ß5 | Level 5 |\n"
"| ¬ß6 | ¬ß7 | Level 5 |\n"
"| ¬ß8 | Drop the first element | Level 6 |\n"
"| ¬ß9 | ¬ß10 | Level 7 |\n"
"| Round-trip | ¬ß11 and ¬ß12 | Level 8 |\n"
"| ¬ß13 | Append element to tuple | Level 9 |\n"
"| ¬ß14 / ¬ß15 | Access snoc'd elements | Level 9 |\n"
"| ¬ß16 | Drop the last element | Level 10 |\n"
"| ¬ß17 | ¬ß18 | Level 11 |\n"
"| ¬ß19 | Reduce function equality to pointwise | Level 12 |\n"
"| Tuple composition | ¬ß20 transforms tuples | Level 13 |\n"
"| Tuples as data | Verify concrete computations on tuples | Level 14 |\n"
"| Cons injectivity | Equal cons'd tuples have equal parts | Level 15 |\n"
"| Snoc injectivity | Equal snoc'd tuples have equal parts | Level 16 |\n"
"| ¬ß21 | Eliminate impossible ¬ß22 | Level 17 |\n"
"| ¬ß23 + case split | Prove ¬ß24 by index | Level 18 |\n"
"| ¬ß25 | Flip an equation | Level 19 |\n"
"| Reconstruction | ¬ß26 + ¬ß27 from head/tail or init/last | Level 20 |\n"
"\n"
"**Proof strategies**:\n"
"- **Index-by-index** (¬ß28 + ¬ß29): when you know each value\n"
"- **Front reconstruction** (¬ß30 + ¬ß31): when you know head + tail\n"
"- **Back reconstruction** (¬ß32 + ¬ß33): when you know init + last\n"
"\n"
"**The big picture**: ¬ß34 models ordered tuples. ¬ß35 builds\n"
"from the front, ¬ß36 from the back. Both have decomposition (tail/init)\n"
"and reconstruction (cons_self_tail/vecSnoc_self_init) identities. Function\n"
"extensionality (¬ß37) lets you prove two tuples are equal index by index.\n"
"The round-trip identities (cons then tail gives back the same tuple, and\n"
"vice versa) mean that ¬ß38 and ¬ß39 form a **bijection**\n"
"between ¬ß40 and ¬ß41. In later\n"
"worlds, you'll formalize this idea as an ¬ß42 (equivalence).\n"
"\n"
"**Where this is going**: Tuples are the building blocks for **big operators**\n"
"like ¬ß43, written ¬ß44 in Lean. Summing the\n"
"entries of a tuple ¬ß45 is exactly what big operators\n"
"do βÄî and that's where this course is headed after Finset.\n"
"\n"
"Next up: the Pset (problem set) world, which will test these skills\n"
"on fresh problems without scaffolding."
msgstr ""

