#: Game.Levels.Fintype
msgid "# Fintype: Counting Elements of Finite Types\n"
"\n"
"You've spent several worlds counting elements of specific finsets βÄî\n"
"using ¬ß0, ¬ß1, ¬ß2, and other ¬ß3\n"
"lemmas. But there's a deeper question: how many elements does an entire\n"
"**type** have?\n"
"\n"
"The answer is ¬ß4 βÄî a typeclass that says a type has finitely many\n"
"elements. When ¬ß5 has a ¬ß6 instance, you get:\n"
"- ¬ß7 βÄî the total number of elements\n"
"- ¬ß8 βÄî the finset of ALL elements\n"
"\n"
"## Why counting types matters\n"
"\n"
"Counting the elements of a type is the foundation of combinatorics in\n"
"Lean. Once you know ¬ß9, you can:\n"
"- **Apply pigeonhole**: if ¬ß10, there is no injection ¬ß11\n"
"- **Detect bijections**: if ¬ß12 and a map is injective,\n"
"  it must be surjective (and vice versa)\n"
"- **Classify finite structures**: two finite groups of the same prime\n"
"  order must be isomorphic\n"
"\n"
"The ¬ß13 typeclass makes all of this machine-checkable.\n"
"\n"
"## The composition rules\n"
"\n"
"The power of ¬ß14 is **composition**: if you know the cardinalities\n"
"of building blocks, you can compute the cardinality of anything built\n"
"from them:\n"
"\n"
"| Construction | Formula | Name |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| ¬ß15 (product) | ¬ß16 | Multiplication principle |\n"
"| ¬ß17 (sum) | ¬ß18 | Addition principle |\n"
"| ¬ß19 (functions) | ¬ß20 | Exponentiation principle |\n"
"| ¬ß21 (subtype) | ¬ß22 | Complement counting |\n"
"| ¬ß23 (equivalence) | ¬ß24 | Bijective counting |\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: Not every type is finite! The natural numbers ¬ß25 have no\n"
"¬ß26 instance. ¬ß27 would be a type error. Finiteness\n"
"is a property that must be established, not assumed."
msgstr ""

