"| ¬ß0 | ¬ß1 | ¬ß2 |\n"
"| ¬ß3 | ¬ß4 | ¬ß5 |\n"
"| ¬ß6 | ¬ß7 | ¬ß8 |\n"
"| ¬ß9 | ¬ß10 | ¬ß11 |\n"
"| ¬ß12 | ¬ß13 | ¬ß14 |\n"
"\n"
"But there's a catch: these rules only work for **finite types** βÄî types\n"
"with a ¬ß15 instance.\n"
"\n"
"Consider the natural numbers ¬ß16. There are infinitely many functions\n"
"¬ß17 (for each natural number, independently choose ¬ß18 or\n"
"¬ß19). The \"formula\" ¬ß20 is meaningless because ¬ß21\n"
"is undefined βÄî ¬ß22 has no ¬ß23 instance. Writing ¬ß24\n"
"in Lean is a type error.\n"
"\n"
"The ¬ß25 constraint in the statement below is what makes the\n"
"counting valid. Without it, ¬ß26 would be a type error.\n"
"\n"
